other_tests.findings: Adjacent to the lateral aspect of the cecum is a 34 x 25 x 17 mm soft tissue density with adjacent inflammatory stranding. Near this inflammatory region is a single diverticulum that is unaffected. There is subtle fat stranding in this region. The appendix appears normal, with a small amount of fluid at the tip, likely representing a reactive change. No obstruction, lymphadenopathy, free fluid, or free air noted.
